{"title_page": "Rangabati", "text_new": "{{copy edit |date=April 2020}}\n'''Rangabati''' is perhaps the most popular recorded song in [[Odisha]]. Jitendra Haripal, who has been awarded with [[Padma Shri]] in 2017 is the male singer of the song.. The song was first recorded for [[All India Radio]] in the mid-1970s. A record company from [[Kolkata]] (then Calcutta), Indian Record Manufacturing Company Ltd (INRECO), then re-recorded the song in 1976. The disc release was delayed due to a dispute and finally released in 1978\u201379.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.odiamusic.com/OMNews/ramesh-mahananda/|title=Enchanting moment with Ramesh Mahananda - \u0b30\u0b2e\u0b47\u0b36 \u0b2e\u0b39\u0b3e\u0b28\u0b28\u0b4d\u0b26\u0b19\u0b4d\u0b15 \u0b38\u0b39\u0b3f\u0b24 \u0b38\u0b3e\u0b15\u0b4d\u0b37\u0b3e\u0b24\u0b15\u0b3e\u0b30 - Odia Music News|website=www.odiamusic.com|access-date=2016-03-25}}</ref> The [[Kosli language|Sambalpuri]] song was written by Mitrabhanu Gauntia and composed by Prabhudatta Pradhan and sung by [[Jitendra Haripal]] and Krishna Patel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/2001/05/27/stories/13270782.htm|title=The Hindu: And the singer sings his song|website=www.hindu.com|access-date=2016-03-25}}</ref> In the 1970s and 1980s the song gained popularity for being played in marriage processions and [[murti]] immersion.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-otherstates/article1823285.ece|title=Welcome break for singer|date=2007-04-04|newspaper=The Hindu|language=English|issn=0971-751X|access-date=2016-03-25}}</ref> The song gained official recognition when it was played in the tableau of [[Odisha]] as part of the [[Republic Day (India)]] celebration in [[New Delhi]] in 2007. The lead singer Jitendra Haripal was felicitated by [[Odisha]] Chief Minister [[Naveen Patnaik]] later that year. The song has also been used as the cheer song during an [[international cricket]] match in [[Barabati Stadium]], [[Cuttack]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120602/jsp/odisha/story_15561051.jsp#.UKdkLmf_m7s|title=I want to keep folk music safe|website=The Telegraph|access-date=2016-03-25}}</ref> \"'''''Rangabati'''''\" was recreated in many other [[languages of India]] and has been recreated in [[Telugu language|Telugu]] for a movie.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.odisha.com/archives/16466|title=\u0b30\u0b19\u0b4d\u0b17\u0b2c\u0b24\u0b40\u0b30 \u0b17\u0b3e\u0b5f\u0b15 \u0b1c\u0b3f\u0b24\u0b47\u0b28\u0b4d\u0b26\u0b4d\u0b30\u0b3f\u0b5f, \u0b15\u0b4d\u0b30\u0b40\u0b37\u0b4d\u0b23\u0b3e\u0b19\u0b4d\u0b15\u0b41 \u0b21\u0b15\u0b4d\u0b1f\u0b30\u0b47\u0b1f \u0b38\u0b2e\u0b4d\u0b2e\u0b3e\u0b28|website=www.odisha.com|access-date=2016-03-25}}</ref>\n\n==In popular culture==\nRangabati is popular in [[Odisha]] and most parts of [[West Bengal]], [[Bihar]], [[Jharkhand]] and [[Chhattisgarh]]. This song is also going to be released in [[Chinese language|Chinese]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ommcomnews.com/odisha-news/-rangabati-song-s-music-composer-prabhudatta-pradhan-passes-away|title=\u2018Rangabati\u2019 Song\u2019s Music Composer Prabhudatta Pradhan Passes Away|last=|first=|date=|website=OMMCOM News|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> {{citation needed|date=July 2015}}\n\nDuring the 7th [[World Water Forum]] at [[Daegu]] in [[South Korea]], Korean dancers danced to the tune of the song.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://m.timesofindia.com/city/bhubaneswar/Social-media-abuzz-as-Korean-girls-dance-to-Rangabati-beats/articleshow/46955156.cms|title=Social media abuzz as Korean girls dance to Rangabati beats - TOI Mobile - The Times of India Mobile Site|website=m.timesofindia.com|access-date=2016-03-25}}</ref> The song is featured in [[Bollywood]] movie ''[[Kaun Kitne Pani Mein]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lyricsbell.com/rangabati-kaun-kitne-paani-mein/|title=Rangabati Lyrics - Kaun Kitne Paani Mein - LyricsBell.com|website=LyricsBell.com|language=English|access-date=2016-03-25}}</ref> directed by Nila Madhaba Panda.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.orissadiary.com/CurrentNews.asp?id=46406|title=Popular Odia song Rangabati new buzz word of Bollywood! Thanks to Nilamadhab Panda, Odisha Current News, Odisha Latest Headlines|website=www.orissadiary.com|access-date=2016-03-25}}</ref> The song was remade by composer [[Ram Sampath]] featuring Sampath himself, [[Sona Mohapatra]], and [[Rituraj Mohanty]] for [[MTV India]]'s [[Coke Studio (India)|Coke Studio Season 4]].<ref name=mtv>{{cite news|title='Rangabati' Promo - Ram Sampath - Coke Studio@MTV Season 4 Episode 4|url=http://www.coca-cola-deutschland.de/videos/rangabati-promo-ram-sampath-coke-studio-mtv-season-4-episode-4-ytxcxww1mpk7k|accessdate=3 July 2015|agency=Coca-Cola Deutschland|date=26 June 2015}}</ref> Nigerian singer Samuel (singh) released a cover version of 'Rangabati' song.<ref>http://incredibleorissa.com/rangabati-samuel-singh/</ref>\n\n== Copyright Controversy ==\nProtests erupted on social media and in [[Western Odisha]] after the telecast of Rangabati remix on MTV Coke Studio on 5 July 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstpost.com/living/coke-studio-version-of-rangabati-weird-rendition-of-cult-oriya-song-sparks-massive-outrage-2329324.html|title=Coke Studio version of 'Rangabati': Weird rendition of cult Oriya song sparks massive outrage|last=|first=|date=|website=Firstpost|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> claiming that the television telecast of this song on Coke Studio did not attribute to the original composer Prabhudatta Pradhan nor did acquire permission from the copyright holder prior to its telecast. Earlier on the same day, a legal notice with a damage claim of ten million Indian Rupees was sent through the [[Supreme Court of India]] to Hindustan [[The Coca-Cola Company|Coca-Cola Beverages]], [[Viacom 18|Viacom18]] Media, Sona Mohapatra, Ram Sampath and Rituraj Mohanty for copyright infringement.<ref name=\"telegraphindia.com\">http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120602/jsp/odisha/story_15561051.jsp#.UKdkLmf_m7s</ref> The petitioner also requested the court to stop the telecast of this remixed song on MTV.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{External links|date=April 2020}}\n*[http://englishdekho.com/rangabati-meaning-in-english/ Rangabati Meaning]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=75GqJMhB-e8 /Rangabati | Original Song & Singer Jitendriya Haripal | Superhit Sambalpuri Folk Songs | Music Box ]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S1xxxLixQIw/ Rangabati Odisha Tourism]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rmEMY0tCD4k/ Korean Dancers tapping feet to Rangabati - Classic hit number of Odisha ]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KKdZ7klDYqE/ Rangabati E Rangbati &#91;Full Song&#93; Sambalpuri Hits- Vol.3 ]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9jiuxDWrVxY/ Rangabati:- Chipmunks Edition]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kptAQ9q9jWI/ Rangabati | Kaun Kitney Paani Mein | Kunal Kapoor, Radhika Apte & Gulshan Grover ]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LKj8m9eZllo/ Cutm Rangabati by Refuse group]\n*[http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x1bi4gv_rangabati-full-video-gadbad-oriya-movie-latest-oriya-film-videos_music/ Rangabati Full Video Gadbad Oriya Movie | Latest Oriya Film Videos]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1D-Vz01KQHc/ RANGABATI~ORIGINAL SONG(RONKGP)]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fuHTpwN8EOI/Sona Mohapatra sings Rangabati @ \"My Jashn\" 2016 Pune for Capgemini]\n*[http://odiapk.in/music/view/23331695/ rangabati MP3]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6KsWIVHT8jY/ rangabati in telugu]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rq-YZMnJKuM&list=PLb4pF9DnVOxWNBs5JqUiLMl2m2NTYXW7w&index=11/ rangabati theme in KICK movie in telugu]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LY_rMXXuJp8/ Rangabati - Ram Sampath, Sona Mohapatra & Rituraj Mohanty - Coke Studio@MTV Season 4]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=09aSRJZ2G3s/Rangabati | Folk Cover | Pragya Patra | Punyaa Productions | A Cover Glorifying Odisha]\